The paper discusses constraint propagation, which is a fundamental technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for solving constraint satisfaction problems (CSPs). The paper also introduces a set of operators for modeling compositions of reduction functions, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the need for integrating static properties of reduction functions, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
